First install a Centos 7 minimal server and setup network &nbsp;

So guide how to get jenkins up and running on centos 7
1. First install it !
yum install -y wgetsudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo http://pkg.jenkins-ci.org/redhat/jenkins.reposudo rpm --import https://jenkins-ci.org/redhat/jenkins-ci.org.keysudo yum install jenkins 2. Install java
sudo yum install java-1.7.0-openjdk &nbsp;
3. Open firewall
&nbsp;
firewall-cmd --zone=public --add-port=8080/tcp --permanentfirewall-cmd --reloadsystemctl enable firewalldsystemctl start firewalldsystemctl status firewalld &nbsp;
4. start it !
sudo /etc/init.d/jenkins restartsystemctl restart jenkins.

